Slides are moved in/out of view by translating the track (`_trackEl.style.transform`) and toggling CSS classes, but no `aria‑hidden` attribute is added/removed. Assistive technologies therefore expose all slides simultaneously.  
Fix (in `_goTo` function):  
```javascript
function _goTo(index, direction) {
  …
  _slides.forEach((slide, i) => {
    const isActive = (i === target);
    slide.el.setAttribute('aria-hidden', String(!isActive));   // add this line
    …
  });
}
```

---

On initialization the first slide is shown but never has `aria‑hidden="false"` set, while the others retain the default (which may be undefined). This can cause ambiguity for screen readers.  
Fix (in `init` after creating slides):  
```javascript
_slides.forEach((slide, i) => {
  slide.el.setAttribute('aria-hidden', i === 0 ? 'false' : 'true');
});
```

